rComments: Robin has a good vision, or so I think. The issue with her teaching is that the curriculum she has created for the course is a recreation of some sort of fantasy. This lack of realism is toxic and I don't think she sees it. She doesn't help you dig deeper into your consciousness but tries to build a non-existent fantasy and imposes it onto you.
Not really great at feedback. Very tough to understand what criteria she bases her grades on.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Amazing, amazing professor. Life Changing Class

Winter version of the happy engineer course. This course is not about leadership at all, instead Robin wishes everyone to create a better version of themselves (self introspection and improvement). Attendance is mandatory due to nature of class. This is one of those courses where she guides you, but how much you can learn is up to you.

Robin is AMAZING. You will 100% get an A in the class if you are ready to go through the dirty work of discovering what you really want from your life. She gives you interesting articles to read that will change your perspective on leadership & your life. This class is about uncovering your authentic self, in doing so you become a great leader
